#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kickstart"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:2
msgid ""
"When you install a {rhel} client, there are a number of questions you need "
"to answer.  To automate installation, you can create a {kickstart} file with "
"all the answers to those questions, so that no user intervention is required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:3
msgid ""
"{kickstart} files can be kept on a server and read by individual clients "
"during installation.  The same {kickstart} file is used to install multiple "
"clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:4
msgid ""
"{kickstart} can be used to schedule a registered system to be installed with "
"a new operating system and package profile, or you can use it to install a "
"new system that was not previously registered, or does not yet have an "
"operating system installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:5
msgid "For more information about {kickstart}, see the Red Hat documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:7
msgid ""
"Some preparation is required for your infrastructure to handle {kickstart} "
"installations.  Before you create a {kickstart} profile, consider:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:8
msgid ""
"A DHCP server is not required for kickstarting, but it can make things "
"easier."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:9
msgid ""
"If you are using static IP addresses, select static IP while developing your "
"{kickstart} profile."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:10
msgid ""
"An FTP server can be used instead of hosting the {kickstart} distribution "
"tree using HTTP."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:11
msgid ""
"If you are performing a bare metal {kickstart} installation, use these "
"settings:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:15
msgid ""
"You need to create a bootable ISO image to be used by the target system for "
"installation.  When the system is rebooted or switched on, it boots from the "
"image, loads the {kickstart} configuration from your {productname}, and "
"installs {rhel} according to the {kickstart} profile."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Building a Bootable ISO"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Copy the contents of [path]``/isolinux`` from the first CD-ROM of the target "
"distribution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:18
msgid "Edit the [path]``isolinux.cfg`` file to default to 'ks'."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:19
msgid "Change the 'ks' section to read:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"label ks\n"
"kernel vmlinuz\n"
"  append text ks=`url` initrd=initrd.img lang= devfs=nomount \\\n"
"    ramdisk_size=16438 `ksdevice`\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:21
msgid "IP address-based {kickstart} URLs look like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "http://`my.manager.server`/kickstart/ks/mode/ip_range\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:23
msgid ""
"The {kickstart} distribution defined via the IP range should match the "
"distribution from which you are building, to prevent errors occurring."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:24
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: If you want to use the [replaceable]``ksdevice``, it looks like:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "ksdevice=eth0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:26
msgid ""
"It is possible to change the distribution for a Kickstart profile within a "
"family, such as {rhel} AS 4 to {rhel} ES 4, by specifying the new "
"distribution label.  Note that you cannot move between versions (4 to 5) or "
"between updates (U1 to U2)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:27
msgid "Customize [path]``isolinux.cfg`` further as required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:28
msgid ""
"For example, you can add multiple options, different boot messages, or "
"shorter timeout periods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:29
msgid "Create the ISO with this command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mkisofs -o file.iso -b isolinux.bin -c boot.cat -no-emul-boot \\\n"
"  -boot-load-size 4 -boot-info-table -R -J -v -T isolinux/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:31
msgid ""
"Note that [path]``isolinux/`` is the relative path to the directory "
"containing the modified isolinux files copied from the distribution CD, "
"while [path]``file.iso`` is the output ISO file, which is placed into the "
"current directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:32
msgid "Burn the ISO to CD-ROM and insert the disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:33
msgid ""
"Boot the system and type [command]``ks`` at the prompt (if you left the "
"label for the Kickstart boot as 'ks')."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:34
msgid "Press kbd:[Enter] to start {kickstart}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Integrating with PXE"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:36
msgid ""
"Instead of using a bootable ISO image, you can use a PXE image instead.  "
"This is less error-prone, allows {kickstart} installation from bare metal, "
"and integrates with existing PXE/DHCP environments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:38
msgid ""
"Upload the {kickstart} profile to the {productname} Server using the "
"{productname} {webui}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:39
msgid ""
"When the {ay} profile has been created, use the URL from the menu:"
"Autoinstallation Overview[] page as the image location."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/kickstart.adoc:40
msgid ""
"For more information about PXE boot, see https://documentation.suse.com/"
"sles/15-SP2/html/SLES-all/cha-deployment-prep-pxe.html."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/package-management.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
